{{Infobox islands |name = Greater Sunda Islands |image_name = |image_caption = |map_image = Greater sunda islands.png |map_caption = |native_name = |native_name_link = |location = [[South East Asia]] |coordinates= {{coord|0|00|N|110|00|E|region:ID_type:isle}} |archipelago = [[Sunda Islands]] |total_islands = |major_islands = |area_km2 = |highest_mount = |elevation_m = |country = [[Brunei]] |country1 = [[Indonesia]] |country2 = [[Malaysia]] |population = |population_as_of = |density_km2 = |ethnic_groups = }}
The '''Greater Sunda Islands''' are a group of four large [[island]]s within the [[Malay Archipelago]]. They are wholly or partly included in present-day Indonesia: [[Java]], smallest but by far the most populous; [[Sumatra]] in the west, directly across the [[Strait of Malacca]] from Malaysia; large [[Borneo]], the Indonesian sector of which is called [[Kalimantan]]; and wishbone-shaped, distended [[Sulawesi]] (formerly Celebes) to the east.<ref>Blij, H. J., & Muller, P. O. (2010). ''Geography: Realms, Regions, and Concepts'' (14th ed.). Hoboken, NJ: J. Wiley & Sons. {{ISBN|0-470-46242-6}}</ref> Under some definitions, only Java, Sumatra and Borneo are included in the Greater Sunda Islands.<ref>Mackinnon, John & Phillipps, Karen (1993). ''A Field Guide to the Birds of Borneo, Sumatra, Java, and Bali : the Greater Sunda Islands,'' Oxford University Press, Oxford ; New York. {{ISBN|0198540345}} (pbk.)</ref><ref>Kennedy, Raymond (1935). ''The Ethnology of the Greater Sunda Islands'', Ph.D. dissertation, Yale University.</ref>
Together with the [[Lesser Sunda Islands]], they make up the [[Sunda Islands]].
== Administration == The Greater Sunda islands are mostly territory of [[Indonesia]]. However, the island of Borneo is divided among the countries of [[Brunei]], Indonesia, and [[Malaysia]]. It contains all of Brunei, the Indonesian provinces of [[Central Kalimantan|Central]], [[East Kalimantan|East]], [[West Kalimantan|West]], [[North Kalimantan|North]], and [[South Kalimantan]], and the Malaysian states of [[Sabah]] and [[Sarawak]] and the federal territory of [[Labuan]].
